# Implement Instapaper-like Themes

The goal is to replicate the reading experience of Instapaper by implementing its four core color themes and adjusting the layout for a focus on readability.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> I have verified these exact hex codes from the Instapaper reader view.

## Proposed Changes

### Styles
#### [MODIFY] [theme.css](file:///d:/yonggeun/porter/git/o-m.kr/src/styles/theme.css)
- Define the four Instapaper themes using CSS variables.
- **Paper** (Classic):
  - Background: `#f4f4f4`
  - Text: `#111111`
- **Coffee** (Sepia):
  - Background: `#f8f1e3`
  - Text: `#5f4b32`
- **Gray** (Dark Gray):
  - Background: `#333333`
  - Text: `#dddddd`
- **Midnight** (OLED Black):
  - Background: `#000000`
  - Text: `#888888`

#### [MODIFY] [global.css](file:///d:/yonggeun/porter/git/o-m.kr/src/styles/global.css)
- Apply the **Coffee** theme variables to the `:root` or `body` by default.
- Adjust typography:
  - Font: Serif for body.
  - Line-height: 1.6.
  - Max-width: 700px.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Start the dev server (`npm run dev`).
- Verify the **Coffee** theme is active.
- Check contrast and readability against the "Instapaper feel".
